Package: embloader
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Embedded Bootloader
 embloader is a modern multi-platform unified boot loader that supports
 various architectures including x86_64, aarch64, riscv64, and others.
 It provides a flexible configuration system for device detection,
 boot menu management, and supports Linux kernel loading with device
 tree overlays.
 .
 Features include:
  - Multi-architecture support (x86_64, ARM64, RISC-V, etc.)
  - systemd-boot / UAPI Boot Loader Specification support
  - SMBIOS-based device detection
  - Device tree and overlay support
  - Configurable boot menus
  - EFI stub loader support
  - Initramfs loading
